reviewText: This is a classic that we hate to love!
One of my favorites of all time!
Very downer story. Won't watch again. Want to buy it back?  Cheap!
At the time it was considered pretty racy, tame by today's standards. Fast moving, nicely acted if a bit cliched.
Very provocative plot for Warner Brothers 1962. Diane McBain is gorgeous. It is an intriguing movie, interesting characters.

One of my favorites movies - Its only been on TV - Best in Acting and Casting
Diane McBain is perfect as "Claudelle Inglish" Don't miss seeing it!

I was in the Navy 1961 to 1965. In 1961 I attended Radioman's School in Bainbridge, Maryland and on the base was a small
theatre. The cost of admission was ten cents and one evening I decided to go see this movie "Claudelle Inglish". Needless to
say I fell in love with Diane McBain and even went back the next evening to see the movie again. However, I can't really recall
the plot or storyline because I was so enamoured by her beauty the rest of the movie was superfluous. I've been looking for
this movie for twenty years and it's only now become available. Thank You Amazon.
